
Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I go to Page 06 of Thoracic MRT

When I select 'Finding' radio button
Then 'Finding' dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Lymph nodes, axilla' from the dropdown menu
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'Borderline, central fat hilus preserved' radio button is enabled
And 'Pathological' radio button is enabled


When I select 'Pathological' radio button
Then 'Right' checkbox is enabled
And 'Left' checkbox is enabled

And 'Signal void' checkbox is enabled

And 'Hemorrhage' checkbox is enabled
And 'Abscess' checkbox is enabled
And 'Necrosis' checkbox is enabled
And 'Vascular contact' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Right' checkbox
Then 'Short axis diameter (SAD)' input field is enabled
And 'Level I' checkbox is enabled
And 'Level II' checkbox is enabled
And 'Level III' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Left' checkbox
Then 'Short axis diameter (SAD)' input field is enabled
And 'Level I' checkbox is enabled
And 'Level II' checkbox is enabled
And 'Level III' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Signal void' checkbox
Then 'Calcification' radio button is enabled
And 'Air' radio button is enabled
And 'Fibrosis' radio button is enabled
And 'Flow void' radio button is enabled

When I go back to Page 03
And I select 'Yes' radio button from Contrast enhanced box
And I select 'Individual' radio button from Sequences box
And I select 'DWI' from 'Weighting' dropdown menu
And I go back to page 06
Then 'Diffusion restriction' checkbox is enabled
And 'Contrast enhancement' checkbox is enabled
